reviews.review_text: Boneless laksa chicken noodle is 18+tax.  The broth was amazing and seems to be made with many ingredients. Their milk tea is good as well, brew on demand and takes 30 mins, just request to add extra milk as it is stronger than other milk tea places.

Something good, quick and satisfying on a rather wet Wednesday evening - and remembered one of our old favourites - city 1; funny how I always forget to review old favourites. This rezzie is perfect as their portions are not generous and suits a weekday dinner. And the Hainanese chicken is as good as in the past, but what s outstanding are their chicken oil rice - Yummy - and the accompanying soup, which is such a good chicken broth that I guess they make from the bones of their boneless chicken. As good as home made chicken soup (oops, my better half is NOT gonna like this remark!). Opted for the half chicken with the 3 bowls of rice and 2 soups. My my my, they still serve  small portions - must be pigmy chickens!! LOL, but the smoothness and flavour makes up for the lack of quantity. And the price - boy it s higher than I remembered it - but what s as cheap now as in the past??!! Oh well!!

Always loved their chicken with rice.  Tried the new menu item today (note: there were 8 pc of tofu) and the tofu was very nicely deep fried with soft centre.  Wish it would have less MSG though.  Hainanese Chicken has also gotten smaller portion, making it a slightly pricy dish now, but overall still very tasty! (PS. a full chicken order comes with 5 bowls of rice.  There is only 3 in pic, they packed the other 2 for us to take away).
Really delicious food and people who work there are very kind
Fast and friendly customer service. Food is excellent. Worth checking are Curry beef on rice, seafood Laksa and authentic boneless Hainanese chicken. Lots of parking space on strip mall.

Great little restaurant! Friendly staff and very tasty satay!! Strawberry ice cream also on point. My daughter (7) enjoyed it so much that she wanted us to leave a 5-star review!:  you should go here. Yum yum!
Hole in the wall kind of restaurant but it s great. Hainanese chicken and Malasian Laksa Noodles are the best!
The best Hainanese chicken rice I have found in Vancouver so far.

Ok, I will admit that I m a HC fanatic.  Had been eating it since I was a kid. So I consider myself a connoisseur of this dish. I was with a friend who I discovered this restaurant. It was a smaller place but don t let that fool you.  The chicken was cooked just right, not overcooked. They also use regular chicken instead of free range chicken, a lot of places serves FR chicken because they can charge more for it.  I definitely will go back again.
Good Singapore style chicken! Also their skewers with the peanut sauce is a must try. Curry chicken and the Malaysian fried noodle for some of their favorite dishes.

Im not sure about the experiences of the other reviewers but Ive ordered their hainanese chicken on a couple of occasions and its really become the go to place for me and my family for hainanese chicken. Good portions, reasonably priced and really delicious. A very modest store but the owners are very nice. Highly recommend to try if youre a fan of hainanese chicken

Their hainanese chicken is very tasty. We ordered a whole chicken and split half the chicken to eat in the restaurant and half to bring home (additional $1.50 for doing that). Its reasonable if you add up the additional sauces and Togo boxes they provide.
Rated the best Singaporean chicken rice in Vancouver.. Good dinner for us!

The boneless Hainan chicken and rice was probably the best Ive had. The texture of the chicken was silky smooth and firm but definitely not stiff. The flavour was just right with or without either dipping sauces. The texture of the chicken rice was soft and fluffy with a little bit of a chew; imagine al dente rice. Nothing was over or under flavoured for us. We will definitely be returning!

1st time trying this Singapore / Malaysian bistro. Its tucked away in an open strip mall by Oak Street and Kind Edward. Fresh, simple and delicious food. The highlight dish was their Laksa with a nice tolerable heat. Love the rice noodles they used...a perfect comfort bowl. Skewers of tender beef, chicken and pork were prepared perfectly as were their string beans and pork. Covid protocols in place. Limited dine-in seating.
Excellent Hainan Chicken. They also cooked the rice in chicken broth. We had half a chicken. It came with 3 bowls of rice & soup.
The boneless Hainan Chicken is delicious! If you order a whole chicken, it comes with two side chicken rice.

I heard their Hainanese boneless chicken was one of the best in town.. courtesy of my mom. As an old adage goes, mom knows best. I did try it and needless to say, it was very good. I bought the whole chicken that comes with 2 large plates of chicken rice (5 bowls according to their menu). I also ordered hot and spicy deep fries tofu and chicken wings. 4 pieces for chicken wings are a tad bit expensive for $8.50. But then again, I was here for the chicken. Final verdict, mom is right. It is very good.
Hainan chicken and laksa are really good.
Hainanese chicken is delicious. Great little spot
Great tasting Hainanese chicken
Best hainanese chicken! Try the curry beef brisket
Best Haianese chicken in town. Love it
Hainanese Chicken boneless is delicious.
Very delicious chicken, roti, curry beef, and lots more. But watch out for gaining weight.
Best Hainanese chicken in Vancouver!
Love the hainanese chicken with oil rice, its a must everytime I visit.
It was down for a while but now the food standard I am pleased to say is up again very nice
Great place! Often come here for their laksa
Best Hainan chicken in town! Cant say more
Best curry beef brisket around, love the place
Famous for their boneless hainan chicken. Must try.
One of the best Haianese Chicken in town
Tasty Singaporean Laksa. Generous size.
Great place to go for delicious boneless hainan chicken
Best Hainan Chicken and milk tea in town
really gooooooooood Hainanese Chicken rice!!
Very good all around will definitely be back

The Hainanese chicken and chicken soup here are good

Enjoyed the meal tremendously!  Greens, beef curry, and their famous hainan boneless chicken.  The beans few slightly spicy, and seasoned nicely, slight spicy, the curry and chicken few excellent!  My only criticism was the fragrant rice was slightly weak, I think it could have been more flavourful.  I would definitely come back

Hidden gem in an old strip mall. The store front isnt popping but food was great. Service is slow as only one person looking after the whole restaurant. The kitchen is also quite slow. Portion is small but tasted delicious. Only comment on the food is the curry beef brisket is chopped into tiny pieces. If the pieces were bigger, it would be perfect.

This restaurant was never on my radar until someone mentioned about their hainanese chicken. Ordered one whole chicken with oil rice and a large curry beef brisket. Pretty good hainanese chicken but I wouldn t say it was the best. The curry beef brisket had a good amount of spice to it but it would be nicer if the beef brisket wasn t cut into super small pieces. Overall a decent meal.
Got a Singaporean food, curry was really delicious.

To be honest. I only come here for the boneless hainanese chicken. They are so delicious. The rice wasnt as oily as before and the service level has dropped a little bit over the years, but the tasty hainanese chicken is one of the best in Vancouver.

Just ate dinner here. Food is very tasty and service is nice. I really liked the bbq satay and the Roti Prata bread with the curry dipping sauce was also really good. The sweet and sour pork on rice is good too. Service is very nice. Only downside is that the place is small.

The Hainanese chicken rice is delicious, portion is a bit small but it s boneless. Their rotis are also very chewy. The milk tea takes 30 mins to brew but it s well worth the wait, it came when we were almost done with the food. Perfect timing. Parking: Busy parking lot but usually can find spot.

Love their signature Hainan Chicken w Oil rice laksa was ok, not bad but we won t come back for this. The appertizer skewers are tender and juicy but more on the sweet side and quite pricey. We didn t feel the after taste of MSG here Service was ok

Located in West King Edward Mall, this cafe will offer you one of the best Hainanese chicken in town.   The half portion comes with three bowls of oil rice, good and hot soup and the two dippings..my favorite ginger oil and the sweet chili vinegar.  The baby bak choy was fresh and perfectly done.   So full that the two satays..chicken  and beef was more than enough for the dinner. I will come back.
